"title": "7632: Twelve, diverse characters of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7632: twelve, diverse characters of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Twelve were men of varied background, gifts and character.</p>\n<h2>The varied backgrounds of the Twelve</h2>\n<p>Peter, Andrew, James and John were fishermen:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:18\">MAT 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:21\">MAT 4:21</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:9\">MAT 9:9</a> <em>Matthew was a tax collector</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:4\">MAT 10:4</a> <em>Simon was a political activist.</em></p>\n<h2>The varied roles of the Twelve</h2>\n<h3>Some took a prominent role in the group</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:9\">GAL 2:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Some played minor but significant roles</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:40-John1:42\">JHN 1:40–1:42</a> <em>Andrew brought Peter to Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:45-John1:46\">JHN 1:45–1:46</a> <em>Philip brought Nathanael</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:20-John12:22\">JHN 12:20–12:22</a> <em>Philip and Andrew brought the Greeks to Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h2>The varied temperaments of the Twelve</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:28\">MAT 14:28</a> <em>Peter was impetuous</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:54\">LUK 9:54</a> <em>James and John were fiery</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:4\">LUK 22:4</a> <em>Judas Iscariot was a traitorous loner</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:25\">JHN 20:25</a> <em>Thomas was cautious.</em></p>\n<h2>The Twelve had a common call to discipleship and witness</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21-Acts1:22\">ACT 1:21–1:22</a></p>\n<h2>The fallibility of the Twelve</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31-Mark8:33\">MRK 8:31–8:33</a> <em>Peter misunderstood</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:14\">MRK 16:14</a> <em>Jesus Christ rebuked the Eleven for not believing reports of his resurrection</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:12-Luke9:13\">LUK 9:12–9:13</a> <em>Jesus Christ tested their reaction to human need</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:8-John14:9\">JHN 14:8–14:9</a> <em>Philip asked the way to the Father.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ gave the Twelve special teaching</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:10-Mark4:11\">MRK 4:10–4:11</a> <em>about his parables</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:35\">MRK 9:35</a> <em>about power and position</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31\">LUK 18:31</a> <em>about his destiny</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ spent his last days and hours with the Twelve</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:11\">MRK 11:11</a> <em>after the triumphal entry into Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:17\">MRK 14:17</a> <em>at the Last Supper</em></p>\n<h2>The Twelve failed Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's concern that they would leave him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:67-John6:70\">JHN 6:67–6:70</a></p>\n<h3>Judas betrayed him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14-Matt26:16\">MAT 26:14–26:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:10\">MRK 14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3-Luke22:4\">LUK 22:3–22:4</a></p>\n<h3>They failed to support him in his final agony of prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:40-Matt26:41\">MAT 26:40–26:41</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:37-Mark14:38\">MRK 14:37–14:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:45-Luke22:46\">LUK 22:45–22:46</a></p>\n<h3>Peter disowned Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:74-Matt26:75\">MAT 26:74–26:75</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:71-Mark14:72\">MRK 14:71–14:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:60-Luke22:61\">LUK 22:60–22:61</a></p>\n<h3>All abandoned Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:56\">MAT 26:56</a> <em>the exception was “the disciple whom Jesus loved”, present at the crucifixion (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:25-John19:27\">Jn 19:25–27</a>)</em></p>",
